    Notes on the next steps for the One-footed-Bride-Tuning repo.

    Keys to remember: 
    Word Wrap: alt-z turns word wrap on and off.
    To find cursor settings, file --> preferences --> cursor settings
    Inside cursor settings, lots of options, including Docs (for Cursor), Indexing and Docs (yours)
    If the files list disappears, press ctrl-b and it comes back. 

    1. Add Docstring, argument types, and return types to all the functions in adaptive_tuning_util.py and diamond_music_utils.py so that when you hover over a library, it is self documenting.
        a. Set up types for all arguments and return values so that the caller knows what to expect.
    Save this for later:
        b. If a function is no longer needed by this repo, it should be commented out, unless you think you might need it soon.

    The Yolo mode, auto-run option. File --> Preferences --> Cursor settings --> Auto-Run Mode. 
    Key to influencing how cursor works is to add context, done with the @ sign. 

