2/13/26 Debugging and Enhancing with Cursor.
    Red highlighted sections (purple on my screen) are code that cursor has removed 
    Green highlights (olive green on my screen) is code that cursor has added. 

    Four modes: Agent, Plan, Debug, Ask
    Highlight a section of code and see at the bottom that you get options to Add to Chat (ctrl-i) or Edit (ctrl-k). For example, I highlighted the previous sentence, and clicked on Edit. This opened a window and a wrote: change alt- to ctrl-, and clicked on accept (I think), and it changed alt-i and alt-k to ctlr-i and ctrl-k in the sentence highlighted. Neat. 
    You can paste files into the chat session, perhaps images copied from web sites, or code library files, narratives. They become context for the model to include in it's answers. 
    She shows how to add more content to the chat session with the Add context button. But mine doesn't have that. I can get it though when I start a prompt with @. 
    Advanced features include lots of things that Claude Code offers, like Rules for how to get certain things done in a manner consistent with your firm's preferences. 

    I wonder if we could use the enhanced simulated annealing paper and github repo to speed up my SA. I could add that doc and codebase to the chat session. I didn't have much success doing that before, but models keep improving. I think early stopping is probabaly already captured most of the efficiency gains of that technique. 
    
    She frequently adds images (random) from unsplash.com. unsplash offers an API to pull random images using RESTful calls with options. 

    Cursor Rules, now in the section Rules, Skills, Subagents. 
    Rules can be global or local to a Project. 
    Model Context Protocol (MCP) For docs on MCP go to http://modelcontextprotocol.io/introduction
    To set up MCP servers, go to Cursor Settings --> Tools & MCP --> Add Custom MCP
    Think if an MCP server that takes care of github actions for you. Imagine that! TO add the github you need the github personal access token. I need to put that in 1Password. Done. 
    Smithery.ai for repository for MCP servers. One click install into cursor or other tools. It asked for my cursor ID, which is based on Google authentication. 
    I created the github token across all repos but I may not have selected read and write access. It appears to be enough, since the new repo was created. This is the prompt: use the github mcp to create a new repo called "github-agent" and add a readme in it with details on Model Context Protocol. It's there: https://github.com/prentrodgers/github-agent
    Neat! Cursor --> Smithery --> Github in less than a minute.
    It's also local here: 
        ls ~/Repos
            One-footed-bride-tuning  github-agent
    Very cool. 

